{"Q0":"Recognize the Pattern:
Pay close attention to how the elements are being compared and moved.

Does the sorting happen one element at a time, like in Insertion Sort?
Are pairs or groups of elements compared, like in Bubble Sort?
Or is the data split and merged, like in Merge Sort?
Identifying the unique "rhythm" of the sort will help you understand its mechanics.

Understand the Process:

Follow each step with purpose. Write down what happens to the data at every stage.
Break it into smaller chunks to make sense of the big picture.
